-- Prysmian Sees Business Recovery Signs in Second Half, Chief Tells Il Sole
-- Sonia Sirletti
-- 2010-06-28T06:23:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/prysmian-sees-business-recovery-signs-in-second-half-chief-tells-il-sole.html

          
          
             Prysmian SpA , the world’s second-
biggest cable maker, sees “clear signs of recovery in the
second  half,” Chief Executive Officer  Valerio Battista  told  Il
Sole 24 Ore  in an interview.  
 “Our volumes, which fell 15 percent to 20 percent in the
first quarter, are now stable,” he was cited as saying.
“Encouraging signs of recovery are coming from South America
and Asia,” Battista told the Italian newspaper.  
